This is a beautiful 1965 Poppy Red Mustang Notchback. She's a 65' Notchback with a 289CU V8 engine with an automatic transmission. I've decoded the VIN number 5F07C634151. The 5 indications the year of production so this Mustang was produced in 1965, the F indicates the location where the car was manufactured in this instance it was made in Dearborn Michigan, the 07 means that the car original started its life out as a coupe 07=Hardtop. The Letter "C" in the Vin indicates  that the car is an original 289-2Y engine. The remaining numbers 634151 stand for the consecutive unit numbers. This car has the original 289 engine in it. The only thing that was changed was at some point the manifold and carburetor were changed from the standard two barrel to a four barrel Edelbrock which makes the car faster and more drivable the four barrel adds additional horsepower. This car comes with a very detailed service history. I have several hard copies of service records spanning a number of years, which is great but it shows how well the owner has treated this mustang. Anytime the car's needed service it has been done from ball joints and suspension to fluid and oil changes.. The interior is virtually flawless with no cracks in the dash or seats. This beautiful Poppy Red 289 1965 Mustang is available for sale today and will surely make its next owner very happy.

The color of this coupe makes it the perfect standout.  A first-year Mustang dressed in red is iconic, but when you render it in a deeper shade of Black Cherry, it gets extra attention when hanging out with the other classics. No matter if you are across the show field or one-inch away, the investment in this color is instantly apparent.  There's a deep luster and the kind of hard shine that makes it look like this coupe has a top coat made of glass.  To pull off this presentation, you also need super straight body panels.  The total effect gives the first-year Mustang's crisp lines a more sophisticated appearance.  That's backed up by the full trim package, including new bumpers and grille to keep everything shining at its best.  Even the bright of the 14-inch styled steel wheels give this one the kind of distinction you're looking for when you want to stand out from the crowd.

Inside the theme of an upgraded classic presentation continues with the two-tone interior.  The white vinyl seats look great, and they just seem to reinforce the clean presentation of this car.  Plus, the carpets are black so you never have to worry about taking your shoes off before hopping in and going for a drive... and that's exactly what this car was built to do.  It has all the right upgrades to keep everyone happy, including the cup holder center console, AM/FM stereo, and R134a air conditioning.  It all makes for a classic cruiser that's comfortable enough for even the daily commute.

Ford's reliable and perky 289 cubic-inch V8 moves the lightweight Mustang enthusiastically through any traffic – especially with the addition of a four-barrel carburetor on top. The engine bay has all the right style upgrades like the bright intake, valve covers, bracer bar, and air topper. There was even a Monte Carlo bar added for extra rigidity and flair.  These motors are extremely reliable, parts are readily available, and performance is very good – all of which gives you an underlying feeling of carefree classic motoring.  Adding to this go-anywhere sensation in this the three-speed automatic transmission and the modern grip of Hankook Optimo tires.

Complete with build receipts and maintenance records, the first-generation Ford Mustang is a true classic car for those who like driving.  Add in the stellar presentation, and you soon realize that vintage style distinction can be quite affordable. Don't miss out, call today!

As you would expect with this high level of restoration, everything works as Ford intended along with the original AM radio and factory A/C. Sale of this time capsule includes the original purchase order, personal checks for deposit and purchase, copy of original window sticker, 1964 California new vehicle registration, copies of titles, original keys and over $33,000 in restoration receipts.
